CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 7, 1959, pg. A20, reads: "Getting the Know - How - Three of the AME Zion 'Miss Pittsburgh District' contestants, who are vying for the honor of representing the Pittsburgh District when the General Women's Home and Foreign Missionary convention meets in Hartford, Conn., this summer, are taking advice from a former winner, Barbara Peace Sowell, who captured the honor four years ago. Left to right: Mrs. Sowell, Gwendolyn Holmes, representing Trimble Chapel Church, Oakdale; Julia Diggs of Trinity AMEZ McKees Rocks, and Mollie Sharpe of Wesley Center. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of former "AMEZ Miss Pittsburgh District" Barbara Peace Sowell on left, and contestants Gwendolyn Holmes, Julia Diggs, and Mollie Sharpe, posed on stairs in interior with two tone walls
